See if you wash your hands well.
We all know that you have to wash them (e.g. when you come home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that to actually get rid of germs, you have to do it the right way.
It's especially important now that the fall infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds to wash enough to remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands.
And most of us wash them less!
Warm water and plain soap are enough - it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise against it).
By washing, we rub not only the bottoms and the top of the hand, but also: fingertips (connected or individually) - rub them with circular movements about the inside of the other hand, spaces between the fingers (twist your hands, rub your fingers against each other), thumbs - each thumb embraces the other hand and in such embraces we spin a moment to the right and left.
In an emergency situation (when hands cannot be washed) we should wipe our hands with a wet tissue and then use antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from 5 zł).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the door or door with your hands washed (recommendation of the Chief Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open it with a paper towel.
The Iranian President says he refused to talk to the United States, Donald Trump denies it.
Tehran did not engage with the U.S. party during the UN General Assembly in New York, despite the offer offered by the Americans to abolish sanctions, said Iranian President Hasan Rowhani on Friday.
U.S. President Donald Trump commented that it was the Iranian side that asked to abolish the restrictions, which he refused to accept.
According to Iranian President Hasan Rowhani, the Americans have proposed to abolish all sanctions imposed on Tehran in exchange for negotiating a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran's nuclear programme and the ballistic missile programme.
Rowhani: Iran will not engage in talks in the atmosphere of maximum pressure
The Iranian President stated that he had refused to take these talks because of the "toxic atmosphere."
He declared that he had met with American diplomats because he was inclined by France, Germany, and the United Kingdom.
However, he stressed that Iran would not engage in talks in an atmosphere of "maximum pressure."
"And even if we want to negotiate with Americans in 5+1 format, no one can predict what the final result will be," said Rowhani.
The day before, the Iranian leader said that he did not rule out talks with the US, and that the European parties to the nuclear agreement were accused of promoting U.S. sanctions against Iran.
He added that the sanctions imposed on Iran following the US withdrawal from the nuclear agreement "are a prerequisite that does not allow for dialogue."
If we can lift this precondition and if America can lift sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America - he declared.
He added that he did not rule out a meeting with President Donald Trump of the United States, even though he did not agree to such a conversation during the last week of the UN General Assembly.
Trump: "Iran asked, I said no."
Donald Trump tweeted that he rejected the Iranian party's request.
"Iran wanted me to abolish the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course I said no!" tweeted the President of the United States.
Voltage with a nuclear agreement in the background
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease the tensions between Washington and Tehran in some form to save the 2015 agreement with Iran, which they were signatories to.
It stated that, in exchange for the abolition of economic sanctions, Iran would abandon the nuclear weapons programme and that the nuclear sector would be under the control of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the withdrawal of the USA from the agreement in May 2015, the other signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to maintain the agreement in force.
It hasn't worked out so far.
Washington is using a tactic of maximum pressure on Iran, and sanctions include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran has announced that if it is not authorised to export raw material, it will limit its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
