The Senate decided on key laws
The Senate adopted without amendment the Law on the disclosure of the family assets of the most important civil servants and on the flights of the most important persons in the State.
52 senators voted in favour of the amendment of the Law on the wealth of families of government officials - without amendments - 14 against, three abstentions.
Thus, the senators decided to reject 12 amendments tabled during the Wednesday debate by Senator Po Sławomir Rybicki.
According to him, the amendments had to "civilise" the law and limit the scope of information given in the declaration on the property situation of own children, the children of the spouse, children adapted to cases where children remain in the common household with the person obliged to make the declaration.
The Law on the transparency of family assets of the most important government officials, whose project was created at the Prime Minister's office, was adopted by the Sejm on 11 September.
The legislation assumes that, among other things, prime ministers, ministers, MEPs, senators, presidents: Constitutional Court, Supreme Administrative Court and Supreme Court, as well as persons headed by other state institutions, will be required to include in the property statement information on the personal property of spouses, children and persons living together.
Nor did the Senate propose amendments to the Law on Flights of the Most Important Persons in the State.
It regulates what flights have the status of HEAD and who can be on board government aircraft with the most important persons in the country.
The Act also specifies who is responsible for keeping the Central Register of Flights.
The law - without amendments - was supported by 55 senators, 12 against, four abstentions.
According to the bill, every president's flight will be a "official mission" flight.
The President will be allowed to accompany family members and others invited by the President.
On the other hand, the flight of the official Prime Minister and the Marshals of the Sejm and the Senate will be only a flight "take place to carry out tasks directly related to the function."
The Act also clarifies the list of persons who can accompany the most important persons in the country during the flight.
According to the regulations, members of the delegation may be on board the aircraft - invited Members, Senators, representatives of public authorities and experts; persons providing technical, medical or organisational services; as well as journalists.
According to the Act, in the event of doubts concerning the flights of the Marshals of the Sejm and the Senate, the head of the KPRM will ask for clarification.
